import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='id', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    top_10_industries = data.nlargest(10, 'rate')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='id', y='rate', data=top_10_industries)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the unemployment rate for the top 10 industries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
